elaxed","children":"XRNotify supports 23+ event types across all major XRPL transaction categories: payments (XRP and issued tokens), NFT operations (minting, burning, offers, transfers), DEX trades (OfferCreate, OfferCancel, AMM operations), trustline changes (TrustSet), escrow events (create, finish, cancel), check operations, and account-level changes like settings modifications and deletions."}]]}],["$","div","How does webhook delivery work?",{"className":"py-8","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white","children":"How does webhook delivery work?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed","children":"When an XRPL transaction matches your configured filters, XRNotify normalizes the event, signs the payload with your webhook secret using HMAC-SHA256, and delivers it as an HTTPS POST to your endpoint. If delivery fails, XRNotify retries with exponential backoff (up to 10 attempts over 12 hours). Events that exhaust all retries are moved to a dead-letter queue for manual inspection and replay."}]]}],["$","div","Is XRNotify free?",{"className":"py-8","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white","children":"Is XRNotify free?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed","children":"XRNotify offers a free tier with 1,000 events per month and 2 webhook endpoints — enough for testing and hobby projects. Paid plans start at $29/month (Starter: 50,000 events, 10 webhooks, WebSocket streaming) and $99/month (Pro: 500,000 events, 50 webhooks, priority delivery). Enterprise plans with custom SLAs are available on request."}]]}],["$","div","How do I verify webhook signatures?",{"className":"py-8","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white","children":"How do I verify webhook signatures?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed","children":"Every XRNotify webhook includes an X-XRNotify-Signature header containing an HMAC-SHA256 hash of the request body, computed using your webhook signing secret. To verify, compute the HMAC-SHA256 of the raw request body with your secret and compare it to the header value using a constant-time comparison function to prevent timing attacks."}]]}],["$","div","Who built XRNotify?",{"className":"py-8","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white","children":"Who built XRNotify?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed","children":"XRNotify was built by Ali Morgan, founder of Jonomor, a systems architecture studio focused on AI Visibility and real-time infrastructure intelligence. XRNotify is the XRPL instrumentation layer of the Jonomor ecosystem, which also includes Guard-Clause, MyPropOps, The Neutral Bridge, Evenfield, and H.U.N.I.E."}]]}],["$","div","Is XRNotify part of a larger ecosystem?",{"className":"py-8","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white","children":"Is XRNotify part of a larger ecosystem?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-3 text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed","children":"Yes. XRNotify is part of the Jonomor ecosystem, a suite of interconnected software products built by Ali Morgan. Within the ecosystem, XRNotify serves as the real-time observation layer — detecting XRPL events at the point of origin before they flow through interpretation and operational layers in other Jonomor properties."}]]}]]}]]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"border-y border-white/5 bg-zinc-900/30 px-6 py-24 lg:px-8 lg:py-32","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"mx-auto max-w-7xl","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl","children":"Articles & Guides"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-6 text-lg text-zinc-400","children":"Technical deep dives into XRNotify, XRPL webhooks, and real-time blockchain monitoring."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className"